objectives:
The automatic generation of radiology reports given medical radiographs has significant potential to operationally and clinically improve patient care. This project will explore the study and development of automated approaches for automatically generating radiology reports, leveraging recent developments in terms of deep learning methods for text generation and image captioning. Experiments will be performed on well-known English datasets (e.g., Open-I or MIMIC-CXR), as well as on Portuguese data from Hospital da Luz.

Goals:

* Study state-of-the-art methods for text generation and image captioning, leveraging deep neural networks;
* Develop and evaluate a novel approach for generating radiology reports in free text;

References:

- Clinically Accurate Chest X-Ray Report Generation ( https://arxiv.org/abs/1904.02633 );
- A Comprehensive Survey of Deep Learning for Image Captioning  ( https://arxiv.org/abs/1810.04020 );

